CORRELATION
OF
BASE
PRESSURE
AND
WAKE
STRUCTURE
OF
SHARP
AND
BLUNTNOSE
CONES
WITH
REYNOLDS
NUMBER
BASED
ON
BOUNDARY
LAYER
MOMENTUM
THICKNESS
IT
HAS
BEEN
ESTABLISHED
IN
THE
PAST
THAT
THERE
IS
A
CERTAIN
RELATIONSHIP
BETWEEN
BASE
PRESSURE
AND
BOUNDARYLAYER
BEHAVIOR
THE
BASEPRESSURE
AND
WAKEFLOW
CONDITIONS
WERE
FOUND
TO
BE
DEPENDENT
UPON
THE
LOCAL
FLOW
CHARACTERISTICS
AT
THE
SURFACE
OF
SUPERSONIC
VEHICLES
DIRECTLY
UPSTREAM
OF
THE
BASE
OR
OF
THE
REGION
OF
WAKEFLOW
SEPARATION
IN
ORDER
TO
USE
EXISTING
DATA
ON
CONES
AND
OTHER
